The paper deals with path prediction for agents in a scene, which is a problem commonly studied in computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The proposed method involves a neural network architecture (cs.LG) that uses attention mechanisms to select relevant regions in the scene (cs.CL). Finally, the paper also discusses the interpretability of the learned model, which is a topic of interest in robotics (cs.RO).
